213
00:21:26,416 --> 00:21:29,208
Are you still here or not? Give me the piece. Come on.

214
00:21:31,875 --> 00:21:34,166
What's taking so long?

215
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:36,833
If this happens, we will all be doomed! Come on!

216
00:21:36,916 --> 00:21:37,916
Yes. We are working on it.

217
00:22:47,041 --> 00:22:48,666
-Head. -Mmm?

218
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:52,625
This is Telmo Reyes Aguirre, a captain of the Spanish Republic.

219
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:56,458
He wants to apply for a review of his trial.

220
00:22:57,583 --> 00:23:02,750
And why are they reconsidering the final verdict regarding treason?

221
00:23:03,416 --> 00:23:06,125
This system never makes mistakes.

222
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:11,250
Because there is no betrayal. And there is no trial.

223
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:17,041
Our only mistake was wanting to go home to our families.

224
00:23:17,125 --> 00:23:18,375
To Spain?

225
00:23:19,333 --> 00:23:22,208
You will definitely be executed on the spot.

226
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,625
