The war is over!

1079
01:58:07,500 --> 01:58:14,500
MAY 8, 1945 - END OF WAR

1080
01:59:42,500 --> 01:59:44,875
Come on! Shoot!

1081
01:59:44,958 --> 01:59:46,958
-Hey! Be careful! -Be careful! He's there!

1082
01:59:49,166 --> 01:59:50,625
Father!

1083
01:59:52,291 --> 01:59:53,458
Please try it!

1084
01:59:54,500 --> 01:59:55,500
Look!

1085
01:59:56,000 --> 01:59:56,833
Who wants it?

1086
01:59:58,000 --> 01:59:59,708
SUMMER 1947

1087
01:59:59,791 --> 02:00:02,041
Hey! Referee!

1088
02:00:02,583 --> 02:00:04,333
-Here! -Referee!

1089
02:00:04,416 --> 02:00:05,541
That's a violation!

1090
02:00:06,875 --> 02:00:08,291
Help!

1091
02:00:08,375 --> 02:00:10,041
Rotten!

1092
02:00:10,125 --> 02:00:13,791
-Referee! -Penalty!

1093
02:00:14,791 --> 02:00:16,000
Unlucky!

1094
02:00:16,083 --> 02:00:17,916
-Down! -I'm down.

1095
02:00:18,916 --> 02:00:20,583
-Help! -Come on. Get up.

1096
02:00:21,333 --> 02:00:23,791
I missed. The sun dazzled my eyes.

1097
02:00:23,875 --> 02:00:26,791
Damn, Dad. Now the sun is bothering you, isn't it?

1098
02:00:26,875 --> 02:00:28,833
Hey! Shut up! Come on, shoot!

1099
02:00:30,625 --> 02:00:31,708
Get it out of there!

1100
02:00:32,500 --> 02:00:33,500
Let's go!

1101
02:00:34,000 --> 02:00:35,000
-Palau! -Eladio!

1102
02:00:35,083 --> 02:00:38,000
-Dad, just steal it! -Damn!

1103
02:00:38,083 --> 02:00:39,083
Greta!

1104
02:00:39,166 --> 02:00:40,750
NO!

1105
02:00:40,833 --> 02:00:42,875
-Come on, shoot! -O'clock!

1106
02:00:42,958 --> 02:00:46,041
Target!

1107
02:00:46,125 --> 02:00:47,458
Palace!

1108
02:00:47,541 --> 02:00:48,875
Barcelona residents, what are you doing?

1109
02:00:48,958 --> 02:00:51,208
-Goal! Come on! -Let go.

1110
02:00:51,291 --> 02:00:53,875
Miners! Goal!

1111
02:00:53,958 --> 02:00:55,083
Look.

1112
02:00:55,833 --> 02:00:59,208
More and more women are leaving. This camp's days are numbered.

1113
02:00:59,291 --> 02:01:01,125
We will be next.

1114
02:01:04,458 --> 02:01:08,625
-Did they say where they are taking you? -Leningrad. Meet us.

1115
02:01:08,708 --> 02:01:12,291
-This. Use this. It's very cold outside. -Palau, he has to go.

1116
02:01:12,375 --> 02:01:14,250
Okay? This. Keep it warm.

1117
02:01:15,000 --> 02:01:16,666
What's his name then?

1118
02:01:19,375 --> 02:01:21,875
-Sorry, but they will leave without him. -Diego.

1119
02:01:21,958 --> 02:01:23,416
I love you, Diego.

1120
02:01:23,500 --> 02:01:25,083
-I love you both. -We love you.

1121
02:01:26,791 --> 02:01:28,583
-Yes, run! -Come on, Palau!

1122
02:01:28,666 --> 02:01:31,208
I'll score next time, I swear. Come on.

1123
02:01:45,666 --> 02:01:48,083
The Kazakhs had invited us to lunch at the kolkhoz.

1124
02:01:48,166 --> 02:01:50,083
for their help in cultivating the plants.

1125
02:01:50,708 --> 02:01:51,791
And?

1126
02:01:52,375 --> 02:01:53,708
Aisulu will also come along.

1127
02:01:56,083 --> 02:01:57,333
So make the best use of it.

1128
02:01:58,291 --> 02:02:00,708
I don't know how much longer they will allow us to leave the camp.

1129
02:02:04,875 --> 02:02:08,041
Which camp? There are only a few of us left here.

1130
02:02:10,375 --> 02:02:11,791
Don't go too far.

1131
02:02:13,125 --> 02:02:14,333
Artigas will cover the costs for you.

1132
02:02:16,791 --> 02:02:17,916
I owe you a debt of gratitude.

1133
02:02:21,583 --> 02:02:22,583
"One," he said.

1134
02:02:24,500 --> 02:02:52,600
Visit Our Telegram Channel:
FILM SUB INDO
@filmsubindonueva

1135
02:02:54,750 --> 02:02:55,750
What's wrong?

1136
02:02:57,083 --> 02:02:59,333
Your thoughts are far from here.

1137
02:03:04,416 --> 02:03:05,916
When we're out of here,

1138
02:03:06,000 --> 02:03:07,875
Come with me.

1139
02:03:22,083 --> 02:03:25,250
This is the land of the Kazakh nation. My land.

1140
02:03:26,250 --> 02:03:28,083
Flowers without roots will not last long.

1141
02:03:35,083 --> 02:03:38,375
I also have a piece of land waiting for me.

1142
02:03:44,333 --> 02:03:45,708
Save it.

1143
02:03:55,750 --> 02:03:58,541
I'll be back to get it.

1144
02:04:00,291 --> 02:04:04,625
The contents are meat. Can be lamb or veal.

1145
02:04:04,708 --> 02:04:09,625
And this is called baursaki. It's like a Spanish churro.

1146
02:04:09,708 --> 02:04:11,416
The main course has arrived!

1147
02:04:11,500 --> 02:04:13,500
Guys, sheep's head

1148
02:04:13,583 --> 02:04:17,833
Served for special, honorable and respected guests.

1149
02:04:18,333 --> 02:04:19,541
Thank You.

1150
02:04:19,625 --> 02:04:21,125
Raqmet.

1151
02:04:21,208 --> 02:04:22,291
Oh, raqmet .

1152
02:04:22,375 --> 02:04:24,458
Raqmet means "thank you" in Kazakh.

1153
02:04:24,541 --> 02:04:25,791
- Raqmet. - Thank You.

1154
02:04:27,083 --> 02:04:28,625
Let's eat.

1155
02:04:40,125 --> 02:04:42,583
It feels good.

1156
02:04:45,125 --> 02:04:48,625
Anara wanted to know who you were before you got here.

1157
02:04:49,750 --> 02:04:53,416
I work in a publication. It belonged to my father, but he was executed.

1158
02:04:53,958 --> 02:04:57,208
It's the only thing left of my family. Until they closed it.

1159
02:05:02,833 --> 02:05:05,666
I once worked as a cook in a hotel in Barcelona.

1160
02:05:05,750 --> 02:05:08,500
And I also like telling jokes. Yes.

1161
02:05:18,000 --> 02:05:20,333
Anara asked if you could tell us one example.

1162
02:05:20,416 --> 02:05:21,833
-Of course. -No!

1163
02:05:21,916 --> 02:05:23,250
-No, don't. -Do!

1164
02:05:23,333 --> 02:05:24,625
It would be best if he didn't.

1165
02:05:24,708 --> 02:05:27,250
-That's a bad idea. -Please do not.

1166
02:05:27,333 --> 02:05:30,916
So, there are kolkhozes, right? Like this one.

1167
02:05:31,416 --> 02:05:34,875
And, suddenly, that bastard Stalin appears, and…

1168
02:05:41,541 --> 02:05:43,500
I told you not to tell it.

1169
02:05:44,000 --> 02:05:46,250
I haven't told you the best part yet. You didn't let me finish my story.

1170
02:05:48,541 --> 02:05:51,041
-You have no sense of humor. Are you serious. -If they are cute…

1171
02:05:51,125 --> 02:05:52,625
Why did they imprison you?

1172
02:05:53,375 --> 02:05:54,583
You never told us.

1173
02:05:55,833 --> 02:05:57,375
Because think differently.

1174
02:06:02,125 --> 02:06:03,291
Whose side are you on?

1175
02:06:04,000 --> 02:06:06,000
None of them.

1176
02:06:06,583 --> 02:06:10,000
I don't have an ideology. I have principles.

1177
02:06:12,708 --> 02:06:17,708
We Kazakhs never imagined this,

1178
02:06:18,333 --> 02:06:22,083
that the world will come here,

1179
02:06:22,875 --> 02:06:25,791
at the gate of our house, but Allah willed it so.

1180
02:06:25,875 --> 02:06:28,833
We are also grateful for that. We thank Allah.

1181
02:06:28,916 --> 02:06:30,125
All praises be to Allah.

1182
02:06:32,458 --> 02:06:33,833
And to our God.

1183
02:06:35,666 --> 02:06:38,208
Whoever can get us out of here first.

1184
02:06:39,458 --> 02:06:40,458
Appropriate.

1185
02:06:47,500 --> 02:06:51,500
Enjoy. We have suffered enough. Please.

1186
02:06:52,458 --> 02:06:55,333
Seven years without eating.

1187
02:06:58,958 --> 02:07:00,333
Please try, Dad.

1188
02:07:07,583 --> 02:07:08,750
Seriously?

1189
02:07:08,833 --> 02:07:10,833
Don't bother me any more with this.

1190
02:07:10,916 --> 02:07:11,916
How do I tell my subordinates?

1191
02:07:12,000 --> 02:07:14,666
No one will help us. Neither Nazarov nor the Communist Party.

1192
02:07:14,750 --> 02:07:16,750
-What? -What about the Blue Division?

1193
02:07:17,625 --> 02:07:20,041
Franco did not want to admit that he had prisoners in the Soviet Union.

1194
02:07:20,125 --> 02:07:22,500
-Not now? -No. There are no prisoners of any kind.

1195
02:07:23,125 --> 02:07:26,166
And the party doesn't want to admit that they sent us here without a trial.

1196
02:07:26,250 --> 02:07:28,208
They say we are deserters.

1197
02:07:28,291 --> 02:07:29,666
Do they want us to rot here?

1198
02:07:29,750 --> 02:07:31,375
Ten, fifteen years? How much longer?

1199
02:07:31,458 --> 02:07:33,083
Impossible. We can't let that happen.

1200
02:07:33,166 --> 02:07:34,208
Calm.

1201
02:07:35,458 --> 02:07:37,041
Nazarov made us an offer.

1202
02:07:37,125 --> 02:07:39,125
Copyright belongs to the Soviet Union.

1203
02:07:39,625 --> 02:07:41,208
We join the revolution.

1204
02:07:42,541 --> 02:07:45,083
-What does it mean? -We become Russian citizens.

1205
02:07:45,166 --> 02:07:47,958
Exactly what we need. Should we also become communists?

1206
02:07:48,041 --> 02:07:50,250
There were no communists left in the Soviet Union.

1207
02:07:50,750 --> 02:07:52,291
Stalin had killed them all.

1208
02:07:53,000 --> 02:07:55,291
Well then, I can go because I'm Russian.

1209
02:07:56,583 --> 02:07:58,083
Your case is different.

1210
02:07:58,916 --> 02:08:03,208
You are here for a violent crime. And absolutely right. You are already a Russian citizen.

1211
02:08:05,333 --> 02:08:07,541
OK, so what does all this mean?

1212
02:08:09,666 --> 02:08:12,208
This means we will work in workshops and factories.

1213
02:08:12,291 --> 02:08:13,958
Then, we will be free.

1214
02:08:14,750 --> 02:08:16,208
But we will be Russian.

1215
02:08:16,958 --> 02:08:18,500
We can't go back to Spain.

1216
02:08:19,625 --> 02:08:21,625
What do you think about all this, Captain?

1217
02:08:24,666 --> 02:08:26,250
I promise I'll get you out of here.

1218
02:08:27,666 --> 02:08:29,291
That doesn't mean we're going to change prisons.

1219
02:08:31,083 --> 02:08:33,166
Your list is very long.

1220
02:08:33,708 --> 02:08:35,750
All prisoners, both Republican and Blue Division,

1221
02:08:35,833 --> 02:08:39,000
from here and other camps. Both men and women.

1222
02:08:40,708 --> 02:08:42,541
The risk is too high.

1223
02:08:42,625 --> 02:08:45,875
There will be a second payment when you arrive in Spain at this address.

1224
02:08:49,875 --> 02:08:51,750
"Clara St…" Is that your family?

1225
02:08:51,833 --> 02:08:55,125
Who cares who they are? They will pay dearly to save us.

1226
02:08:57,708 --> 02:08:58,916
Damn.

1227
02:09:07,458 --> 02:09:08,458
Good.

1228
02:09:23,375 --> 02:09:25,625
Can we trust those Nazis?

1229
02:09:27,958 --> 02:09:30,083
-Iván José González. -No one blames you, buddy.

1230
02:09:31,458 --> 02:09:32,458
Thank You.

1231
02:09:39,166 --> 02:09:41,250
-Take care of yourself well. -You too.

1232
02:09:43,625 --> 02:09:44,958
Roland Durban.

1233
02:09:45,583 --> 02:09:46,583
Eladio.

1234
02:09:56,416 --> 02:09:57,500
I am really, really sorry.

1235
02:10:00,333 --> 02:10:02,166
-Claude Gaspard. -Palau.

1236
02:10:07,166 --> 02:10:08,375
We will miss you.

1237
02:10:09,708 --> 02:10:10,583
Me, too.

1238
02:10:11,083 --> 02:10:13,041
Have a nice trip. Thank You.

1239
02:10:15,458 --> 02:10:17,291
-See you. -Young Busacca.

1240
02:10:17,375 --> 02:10:19,833
-May God be with you. -Good luck.

1241
02:10:21,916 --> 02:10:24,083
O! Barcelona resident.

1242
02:10:27,375 --> 02:10:28,375
Another.

1243
02:10:30,375 --> 02:10:32,458
How to say "paratrooper" in Russian?

1244
02:10:33,041 --> 02:10:34,875
André Monicelli.

1245
02:10:34,958 --> 02:10:36,291
"Parachute flutter."

1246
02:10:38,250 --> 02:10:39,375
What? Bad joke?

1247
02:10:41,000 --> 02:10:42,000
Very bad.

1248
02:10:47,041 --> 02:10:48,375
Take care of your family.

1249
02:10:49,458 --> 02:10:50,458
I will.

1250
02:10:51,958 --> 02:10:52,958
Goodbye.

1251
02:10:57,541 --> 02:10:59,708
Luciano Craspelli.

1252
02:11:05,750 --> 02:11:08,208
Look how quickly the fascists changed sides.

1253
02:11:13,875 --> 02:11:15,291
Melléin Palau.

1254
02:11:20,625 --> 02:11:22,583
Hey, soldier. Turn the shirt pocket inside out.

1255
02:11:26,083 --> 02:11:27,791
They were searching them.

1256
02:11:27,875 --> 02:11:30,541
If they find Müller's list, we're done.

1257
02:11:35,416 --> 02:11:36,708
What is he doing?

1258
02:11:37,708 --> 02:11:40,583
-What is he doing? -Hey! Back in line!

1259
02:11:43,458 --> 02:11:45,958
I told you, Captain. I told you.

1260
02:11:46,041 --> 02:11:47,833
-Line up! -And he still received the money.

1261
02:11:47,916 --> 02:11:51,250
-He gave them the list. -What is he holding there? Give it to me.

1262
02:11:51,333 --> 02:11:52,416
Let me see.

1263
02:11:54,750 --> 02:11:56,916
Those Nazi bastards won't get away with it.

1264
02:11:58,166 --> 02:12:00,291
-Junqueras, stop. -Müller!

1265
02:12:00,833 --> 02:12:01,916
Fascist bastards!

1266
02:12:02,000 --> 02:12:03,291
-Wait. -I will kill him! Let me go!

1267
02:12:03,375 --> 02:12:04,666
-Captain. -Let me go!

1268
02:12:05,250 --> 02:12:08,208
Let me go! Bastard! Let me go!

1269
02:12:08,291 --> 02:12:11,416
Let me go! Damn you!

1270
02:12:11,500 --> 02:12:12,500
-Oh my... -Wait.

1271
02:12:12,583 --> 02:12:13,583
Guard!

1272
02:12:13,666 --> 02:12:15,791
Eladio!

1273
02:12:18,416 --> 02:12:19,416
Junqueras.

1274
02:12:19,916 --> 02:12:20,916
Did you get shot?

1275
02:12:22,291 --> 02:12:23,625
OK, you're fine.

1276
02:13:12,666 --> 02:13:15,333
Remember, Lord, that we are but dust.

1277
02:13:16,041 --> 02:13:19,666
And man is like the grass and flowers of the field that wither.

1278
02:13:19,750 --> 02:13:20,750
And…

1279
02:13:21,583 --> 02:13:22,583
And…

1280
02:13:34,083 --> 02:13:38,291
"With thundering music I come, with my cornet and drums...

1281
02:13:40,250 --> 02:13:43,458
I don't play marching songs just for the recognized winners."

1282
02:13:44,166 --> 02:13:46,750
"I play marching songs for the conquered and murdered people."

1283
02:13:48,083 --> 02:13:49,250
"Have you heard?"

1284
02:13:50,375 --> 02:13:52,416
that winning the day was a good thing?"

1285
02:13:54,333 --> 02:13:58,166
"I also said that falling is good."

1286
02:14:01,708 --> 02:14:04,791
"I hit and hit the dead."

1287
02:14:06,750 --> 02:14:08,500
"Goodbye to those who fail."

1288
02:14:08,583 --> 02:14:12,250
"And for those whose warships sank. And for those who themselves drowned."

1289
02:14:13,541 --> 02:14:16,041
"And countless unknown heroes

1290
02:14:16,666 --> 02:14:18,291
the same as

1291
02:14:19,875 --> 02:14:22,166
the greatest heroes known."

1292
02:14:26,916 --> 02:14:29,875
MADRID MINISTRY OF FOREIGN AFFAIRS

1293
02:14:29,958 --> 02:14:33,041
Please, sir. Just a moment.

1294
02:14:33,125 --> 02:14:36,291
-Again? No, not again. Impossible. -Excuse me. It's just...

1295
02:14:42,291 --> 02:14:44,291
What do you want? Can't you see I'm busy?

1296
02:14:44,791 --> 02:14:48,625
He returns. He's still there. He said he won't leave until you see him.

1297
02:14:48,708 --> 02:14:50,541
-What does he want? -I don't know.

1298
02:14:51,666 --> 02:14:53,583
Hey, no. You shouldn't be here. No!

1299
02:14:54,541 --> 02:14:56,375
OK, what do you want?

1300
02:14:56,875 --> 02:14:58,208
Do you know how to write?

1301
02:14:58,291 --> 02:15:00,791
-Yes. So what? -Then, note this down.

1302
02:15:01,875 --> 02:15:03,125
Esperanza Moreno.

1303
02:15:03,625 --> 02:15:04,791
Antonio Castillo.

1304
02:15:05,291 --> 02:15:07,041
Antonio Barba Penas.

1305
02:15:07,125 --> 02:15:08,708
Cesar Benítez Martinez.

1306
02:15:09,583 --> 02:15:11,291
Pablo Espinoza Gomez.

1307
02:15:12,125 --> 02:15:13,458
Abelino González.

1308
02:15:14,916 --> 02:15:17,208
Tomás Bernal Aroca.

1309
02:15:27,666 --> 02:15:29,291
Diego Salgado Jarque.

1310
02:15:34,375 --> 02:15:36,375
Manuel Fernández Collado.

1311
02:15:41,916 --> 02:15:43,833
Pablo Fernández Carrasco.

1312
02:15:48,375 --> 02:15:50,458
Eladio Taraño Junqueras.

1313
02:15:51,458 --> 02:15:52,875
Good grief.

1314
02:15:54,083 --> 02:15:55,833
Telmo Reyes Anguera.

1315
02:15:57,166 --> 02:15:59,333
Francisco de Asis Moreno Santos.

1316
02:16:07,666 --> 02:16:08,666
Father.

1317
02:16:20,125 --> 02:16:21,166
I am very happy.

1318
02:16:46,000 --> 02:16:47,250
You're going home.

1319
02:16:48,041 --> 02:16:51,375
Yes. We both deserve enough rest.

1320
02:16:53,416 --> 02:16:54,458
Is not it?

1321
02:16:59,166 --> 02:17:04,583
Despite everything that has happened, it has been a pleasure getting to know you.

1322
02:17:05,666 --> 02:17:06,791
bro.

1323
02:17:16,666 --> 02:17:19,416
See you later, Camp Leader.

1324
02:18:00,208 --> 02:18:01,666
I can already smell it.

1325
02:18:01,750 --> 02:18:03,083
What? Fabada?

1326
02:18:03,166 --> 02:18:04,541
Oh Lord.

1327
02:18:04,625 --> 02:18:05,708
What is fabada?

1328
02:18:05,791 --> 02:18:07,833
-You don't know what fabada is? -No.

1329
02:18:07,916 --> 02:18:11,958
Beans, bacon, chorizo… It's the best thing in the world, Pablín.

1330
02:18:12,041 --> 02:18:14,125
Antonio Barba Penas.

1331
02:18:20,458 --> 02:18:22,416
Adelino González.

1332
02:18:24,958 --> 02:18:25,958
Captain.

1333
02:18:28,375 --> 02:18:31,125
-Lieutenant. -Martin Marias.

1334
02:18:32,916 --> 02:18:34,458
I didn't expect you to stay.

1335
02:18:36,958 --> 02:18:38,208
I didn't expect you to leave.

1336
02:18:38,708 --> 02:18:40,208
Angel Turion.

1337
02:18:46,541 --> 02:18:48,208
David Obeso.

1338
02:18:55,833 --> 02:18:57,375
José de la Torre.

1339
02:18:57,458 --> 02:18:58,458
Thank You.

1340
02:18:59,708 --> 02:19:01,833
Have a nice trip. Take care of yourself well.

1341
02:19:04,166 --> 02:19:07,000
-Captain. -Domingo Correa Martinez.

1342
02:19:08,916 --> 02:19:10,041
Are you sure?

1343
02:19:12,125 --> 02:19:13,125
Yes.

1344
02:19:13,666 --> 02:19:15,333
Diego Salgado.

1345
02:19:18,625 --> 02:19:20,000
This is my home now.

1346
02:19:21,125 --> 02:19:23,916
-Take good care of everything, okay? -Thanks for everything, my friend.

1347
02:19:29,250 --> 02:19:31,000
Eladio Junqueras.

1348
02:19:33,583 --> 02:19:34,583
Now it's my turn.

1349
02:19:35,541 --> 02:19:36,541
In progress.

1350
02:19:37,708 --> 02:19:38,916
I'll keep you here, okay?

1351
02:19:48,250 --> 02:19:49,333
Pablito.

1352
02:19:52,708 --> 02:19:53,833
Take care of yourself.

1353
02:19:53,916 --> 02:19:55,500
-Pablo Fernandez. -Personal!

1354
02:19:56,291 --> 02:19:59,291
This kid isn't going anywhere. Remove his name from the list.

1355
02:19:59,375 --> 02:20:01,000
Hey! What are you doing?

1356
02:20:02,083 --> 02:20:04,000
-The boy… -Captain.

1357
02:20:04,083 --> 02:20:07,583
The boy was a Soviet citizen, like all the minors held in the camp.

1358
02:20:07,666 --> 02:20:10,916
-Captain, what happened? -Here are the documents. See for yourself.

1359
02:20:12,291 --> 02:20:13,166
Telmo.

1360
02:20:13,958 --> 02:20:14,958
I can't go back?

1361
02:20:17,791 --> 02:20:19,291
How legitimate is this?

1362
02:20:19,375 --> 02:20:23,041
It is legal enough to cancel the extradition.

1363
02:20:23,541 --> 02:20:24,833
-Telmo… -You bastard.

1364
02:20:27,583 --> 02:20:28,583
Hey! Boy!

1365
02:20:28,666 --> 02:20:31,000
-No! I'll do it. -Don't you dare let him get on the bus.

1366
02:20:31,083 --> 02:20:32,083
Yes.

1367
02:20:32,166 --> 02:20:35,208
-Pablito. -No. Leave me alone.

1368
02:20:35,291 --> 02:20:38,125
Leave me alone! I want to go back!

1369
02:20:38,208 --> 02:20:39,666
-Pablo! -Leave me alone, please!

1370
02:20:39,750 --> 02:20:40,750
Pablo.

1371
02:20:45,125 --> 02:20:47,625
Learn about the kings and queens of Spain. Okay?

1372
02:20:47,708 --> 02:20:49,458
What? What are you talking about?

1373
02:20:49,541 --> 02:20:50,625
Enter.

1374
02:20:52,875 --> 02:20:55,500
Come on. Pablito, hurry up.

1375
02:21:00,125 --> 02:21:01,125
Drive.

1376
02:21:05,458 --> 02:21:08,291
Can you explain what is going on here?

1377
02:21:11,500 --> 02:21:12,750
The bus will leave soon.

1378
02:21:13,250 --> 02:21:16,000
I'll drive to the next checkpoint,

1379
02:21:16,083 --> 02:21:18,958
Show me the documents there, and take the boy with me. Understand?

1380
02:21:23,041 --> 02:21:24,291
These documents?

1381
02:21:29,916 --> 02:21:31,916
What the hell do you think you're doing?!

1382
02:21:32,708 --> 02:21:33,833
Guard!

1383
02:21:41,125 --> 02:21:42,458
Get rid of him.

1384
02:22:27,625 --> 02:22:32,291
MADRID 1982

1385
02:22:50,041 --> 02:22:51,916
400 pesetas to be exact.

1386
02:22:56,208 --> 02:22:57,750
Is this your first visit to Spain?

1387
02:23:10,125 --> 02:23:13,666
They will have the power to be consulted.

1388
02:23:13,750 --> 02:23:16,750
regarding whether they want to be part of a military bloc.

1389
02:23:18,125 --> 02:23:19,916
Reject NATO! No military bases!

1390
02:23:20,000 --> 02:23:23,500
We don't want any military bloc.

1391
02:23:23,583 --> 02:23:26,083
Yankees are out!

1392
02:23:34,000 --> 02:23:35,666
Good afternoon, Lieutenant.

1393
02:23:39,041 --> 02:23:40,833
I'm Reyes.

1394
02:23:42,166 --> 02:23:44,291
Captain Telmo Reyes.

1395
02:24:23,875 --> 02:24:25,083
He…

1396
02:24:26,541 --> 02:24:28,000
He kept it all his life.

1397
02:24:32,041 --> 02:24:33,833
And he wants you to have it.

1398
02:25:50,708 --> 02:25:51,708
Captain.

1399
02:25:59,500 --> 02:26:00,708
Lieutenant.

1400
02:26:12,583 --> 02:26:13,791
Captain.

1401
02:26:26,250 --> 02:26:28,083
Remember what Oraz used to say?

1402
02:26:29,375 --> 02:26:33,458
"No man is freer than he who has ever been imprisoned."

1403
02:26:34,250 --> 02:26:37,416
FOR MY MOTHER

1404
02:26:37,500 --> 02:26:40,375
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING

1405
02:26:43,000 --> 02:26:49,833
Ceasefire

1406
02:26:51,500 --> 02:27:50,600
